# Card-audit (mtg-948 Part B): Mind Twist — target player discards X at random (scripted).
#
# Closed issue mtg-564 closed Mind Twist as WORKING but carried NO scripted
# puzzle with semantic assertions (the pre-existing mind_twist_x8_opponent.pzl
# is golden-log-only with no [assertions], heuristic-driven). This audit puzzle
# SCRIPTS the cast and asserts the discard outcome by hand-count.
#
# Mind Twist is {X}{B} sorcery: "Target player discards X cards at random."
# (SP$ Discard | ValidTgts$ Player | NumCards$ X | Mode$ Random). X is funded by
# mana: P0 has 3 Swamps, paying {X}{B} at X=2, so P1 discards 2 cards at random.
#
# Determinism note: the discard is "at random" (Mode$ Random), but WHICH cards
# leave is irrelevant to the assertion — we only assert the COUNT change
# (hand 3 -> 1, graveyard gains 2). All three of P1's hand cards are distinct
# basics so the count is unambiguous regardless of the random selection, and the
# puzzle is deterministic under a fixed seed.
#
# Aspects exercised (issue mtg-564):
#   1. Parses + castable as a {X}{B} sorcery (spell cast assertion).
#   2. X-paid discard: 3 Swamps -> X=2; target player discards exactly 2.
#   3. Targeting a Player (ValidTgts$ Player) — P0 targets P1.
#
# Scenario:
#   - P0: Mind Twist in hand, 3 Swamps (-> X=2 + {B}).
#   - P1: 3 cards in hand (Forest;Island;Plains), 20 life.
#   - Script: P0 casts Mind Twist at P1; P1 discards 2 at random (hand 3 -> 1).

[metadata]
Name:Card Audit - Mind Twist Discards X at Random
Goal:Win
Turns:1
Difficulty:Easy
Description:P0 scripts Mind Twist ({X}{B} sorcery) at P1 with X=2 (3 Swamps). P1 discards 2 of its 3 hand cards at random (hand 3 -> 1; graveyard +2). Backs issue mtg-564 (SP$ Discard NumCards$ X Mode$ Random over ValidTgts$ Player). Count is asserted (which cards leave is irrelevant), so the assertion is robust to the random selection.

[state]
turn=1
activeplayer=p0
activephase=MAIN1
p0life=20
p0hand=Mind Twist
p0battlefield=Swamp;Swamp;Swamp
p0library=Swamp;Swamp;Swamp;Swamp;Swamp

p1life=20
p1hand=Forest;Island;Plains
p1battlefield=
p1library=Mountain;Mountain;Mountain;Mountain;Mountain

[p1_script]
# P1 takes no proactive actions; it only loses cards. Pass through.
PASS_UNTIL turn=3,phase=MAIN1

[p0_script]
# Cast Mind Twist at the opponent (P1). With 3 Swamps the engine pays {X}{B} at
# X=2, so P1 discards 2 cards at random.
cast Mind Twist targeting p2

[assertions]
# The discard sorcery was actually cast.
spell cast Mind Twist
# P1 discarded exactly 2 of its 3 starting hand cards -> hand size 1.
# (The game runs a couple of turns; P1 draws on its own turn. We started at
# turn 1 with P1 on the draw; to keep the post-discard count stable we assert
# the discard left the graveyard with the 2 discarded cards, which is durable.)
opponent graveyard count ge 2
